OL,6,FOver the weekend, government sources
OL,7,Findicated that Kendall's reforms would
OL,8,Finclude a "right to try guarantee"
OL,9,Fthat would allow disabled people to
OL,10,Fenter employment without risk of
OL,11,Flosing their benefits if it did not
OL,12,Fwork out.
OL,14,FBut Conservative shadow work and
OL,15,Fpensions secretary Helen Whately said
OL,16,FLabour was "divided" over welfare and
OL,17,F"cannot deliver the decisive change we
OL,18,Fneed".
